This repo leverage golang built-in ssh to implement the following tools:

$ git clone git@github.com:mllu/go-ssh.git
$ cd go-ssh

ssh
  how to use?
  $ cd cmd/ssh; go build;
  Usage of ./ssh:
    -cmd string
        command to execute on remote server (default "pwd")
    -key_file string
        location of private key (default "/Users/user/.ssh/id_rsa")
    -login_host string
        hostname to ssh (default "localhost")
    -login_port string
        port to ssh (default "22")
    -login_user string
        username to ssh login (default "user")

shell
  how to use?
  $ cd cmd/shell; go build;
  Usage of ./shell:
    -key_file string
        location of private key (default "/Users/user/.ssh/id_rsa")
    -login_host string
        hostname to ssh (default "localhost")
    -login_port string
        port to ssh (default "22")
    -login_user string
        username to ssh login (default "user")

multi-tail
  how to use?
  $ cd cmd/multi-tail; go build;
  please refer to cmd/multi-tail/README for more info

